{{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Aggie Softball Complex| nickname = | image = | address = Olsen Blvd and Tom Chandler Rd | location = [[College Station, Texas|College Station]] [[Texas]], United States 77840 | coordinates = {{coord|30.604674|-96.3435959|format=dms|display=inline,title|region:US_type:landmark}} | opened = March 30, 1994 | closed = April 15, 2018| demolished = | owner = [[Texas A&M University]] | operator = [[Texas A&M University]] | surface = Tifway 419 [[Bermuda Grass]] | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Texas A&M Aggies softball]] ([[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]]) (1994-2018) | seating_capacity = 1,750 | record_attendance = 2,341 (April 27, 2005 vs [[Texas Longhorns softball|Texas Longhorns]]) | dimensions = 190ft (LF/RF), 220ft (CF) }} The '''Aggie Softball Complex''' was the home to the [[Texas A&M Aggies softball|Texas A&M Aggies softball team]] from 1994 to 2018. The stadium was dedicated on March 30, 1994. The final game played in the Aggie Softball Complex was April 15, 2018, a military appreciation game, against the Kentucky Wildcats. The record attendance for the complex is 2,341, set on April 27, 2005 versus the Texas Longhorns. Nineteen of the 20 highest attendance numbers were set during the 2005, 2006, and 2007 seasons. The stadium has hosted [[NCAA]] Regionals in 2005, 2007, 2008, 2011, 2012, 2013 and 2017 and NCAA Super Regionals in 2007 and 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aggie Softball Complex|url=http://www.12thman.com/ViewArticle.dbml?SPSID=632690&SPID=93238&&&DB_OEM_ID=27300&ATCLID=205237680&DB_OEM_ID=27300|publisher=Texas A&M University|accessdate=January 14, 2015}}</ref>
The Aggie Softball team now plays in the Davis Diamond which is located nearby.
