{{infobox country at games | NOC = BOL | NOCname = [[Bolivian Olympic Committee]] | games = Olympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.comiteolimpicoboliviano.org.bo }}&nbsp;{{es icon}} | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Bolivia|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Bolivia|competition=Winter Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | seealso = }} '''[[Bolivia]]''' first participated at the '''[[Olympic Games]]''' in 1936. The nation has sent athletes to compete in every [[Summer Olympic Games]] since 1964, except when they participated in the [[American-led boycott of the 1980 Summer Olympics]]. The nation has also participated in the [[Winter Olympic Games]] on several occasions since 1956, but not since 1992.
To date, no athlete from Bolivia has ever won an Olympic medal, making it the only South American country never to do so.<ref>[https://www.irishexaminer.com/breakingnews/sport/meet-the-worst-ever-olympic-nations--and-how-some-of-them-could-finally-win-a-medal-in-rio-747579.html]</ref> However, the National U15 Football team has won a gold medal for the country at the [[Youth Olympic Games]] in Singapore 2010.
