{{Infobox MMA event | name = Insomnia Summer Show | image = | promotion = Attila Gergely | date = July 18, 2009 | venue = [[Stadionul Olimpia]] | city = [[Satu Mare]], [[Romania]] {{flagicon|Romania}} | attendance = 2,500 | gate = | buyrate = | previousevent = | followingevent = }}
The '''Insomnia Summer Show''' was an event held by [[Insomnia Club]] and [[Attila Gergely]] on Saturday, July 18, 2009 at the [[Stadionul Olimpia|Olimpia Stadium]] in [[Satu Mare]], [[Romania]].<ref name="Show">{{cite web|url=http://www.informatia-zilei.ro/new/2009/07/08/insomnia-summer-show-cu-cage-fight-pe-stadionul-olimpia/|title=Insomnia Summer Show cu Cage Fight pe Stadionul Olimpia|date=8 July 2009|publisher=Informaţai Zilei|language=Romanian|accessdate=20 July 2009}}</ref> It featured a [[beauty contest]], a [[martial arts]] tournament and three concerts. The announcer for the show was the famous [[Romania]]n actor and comedian [[Sorin Tănase]] from [[Baia Mare]].
The [[beauty contest]] was free to join and many local participants enrolled, including models from the modelling agency, Gaby's Models.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaby-models.ro/|title=Gaby's Models|publisher=www.gaby-models.r|language=Romanian|accessdate=20 July 2009}}</ref> There were three concerts held, the first concert was from the [[Hungary|Hungarian]] rock band [[Slager Duo]], the second was performed by [[La Familia (rap group)|La Familia]] hip-hop singer Puya and the last concert which closed the event was performed by the [[Romania]]n [[electronic rock]] group [[Voltaj]].<ref name="Show"/>
One of the main events of the show was the [[martial arts]] tournament which featured five [[mixed martial arts]] (MMA) fights that took place in an eight-sided cage located in the middle of the stadium. There were only two categories, under and over {{convert|85|kg|lb|abbr=on}}. The referees were Vasile Fușle and Gergely Attila, notable national and international [[judo]] referees.<ref name="Peste">{{cite web|url=http://www.informatia-zilei.ro/new/2009/07/20/peste-2-500-de-satmareni-la-concertul-puya-%C8%99i-voltaj/|title=Peste 2.500 de sătmăreni la concertul Puya și Voltaj|date=20 July 2009|publisher=Informaţai Zilei|language=Romanian|accessdate=20 July 2009}}</ref> The first match was between Cristian Pintea and Cristian Nichita, two kick-boxing contenders that ended after five minutes after Nichita submitted from Pintea's rear naked choke.<ref name="Peste"/>
The following two matches ended with a unanimous decision from the referees.<ref name="Peste"/> The fourth match was the shortest in the tournament, ending after only seven seconds when Raul Maghiar broke his foot after a [[Throw (grappling)|throw]] from the winner Zenobiu Mic, a judoka.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazetanord-vest.ro/index_files/sport.htm |title=Match 4 |publisher=Gazeta de Nord Vest |language=Romanian |accessdate=20 July 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070503095737/http://www.gazetanord-vest.ro/index_files/sport.htm |archivedate=May 3, 2007 }}</ref> The last match was the second shortest, lasting two minutes, the winner being Gică Apostu with a submission technique called a guillotine.<ref name="Peste"/>
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Winner ! Loser ! Method |- | {{flagicon|ROU}} '''Cristian Pintea''' | {{flagicon|ROU}} Cristian Nichita | Submission (Rear Naked Choke) |- | {{flagicon|ROU}} '''Varga Attila''' | {{flagicon|ROU}} Valentin Nistea | Unanimous Decision |- | {{flagicon|ROU}} '''Adrian Vălean''' | {{flagicon|ROU}} Dobó Szilárd | Unanimous Decision |- | {{flagicon|ROU}} '''Zenobiu Mic''' | {{flagicon|ROU}} Raul Maghiar | KO (broken foot) |- | {{flagicon|ROU}} '''Gică Apostu''' | {{flagicon|ROU}} Romeo Dana | Submission (Guillotine) |}
