{{coord| 41.993249|21.464866|display=title}} {{Infobox stadium |stadium_name = Sportskiot Centar "Jane Sandanski" |nickname = "Luxury Arena" |image = [[File:JaneSandanski.png|350px|arena]] |caption = Jane Sandanski Arena 2014 |location = [[Aerodrom Municipality, Macedonia|Aerodrom]], [[Skopje]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] |broke_ground = |opened = 1980s |demolished = 2012 |reopened = 2014 |owner = [[RK Vardar]] |operator = |construction_cost = 15 000 000 [[euros]] |chief engineer = |tenants = [[RK Vardar]] / [[KK MZT Skopje Aerodrom|MZT Skopje Aerodrom]] |former_names = |seating_capacity = 6.500 ||closed = 15 February 2013}}
'''Jane Sandanski Arena''' ({{lang-mk|Спортскиот центар "Јане Сандански"}} or {{lang|mk|Сала "Јане Сандански"}}) is an indoor sports arena located in the [[Aerodrom Municipality (Skopje)|Aerodrom Municipality]] of [[Skopje]], [[Republic of Macedonia]]. It has a capacity of 6,500. It is named after the Macedonian revolutionary [[Yane Sandanski|Jane Sandanski]].
On 18 November 2012, it was announced that the arena would be completely demolished, with a new arena called Sports Centre Jane Sandanski planned to be built in its stead.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kajgana.com/promoviran-proektot-za-noviot-sportski-centar-jane-sandanski%E2%80%9C |title=Комплетна реконструкција на "Јане Сандански" |first= |last= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130122082453/http://kajgana.com/promoviran-proektot-za-noviot-sportski-centar-jane-sandanski%E2%80%9C |archivedate=2013-01-22 |df= }}</ref> On 14 February 2013, MZT Skopje held their last training in Jane Sandanski, with more than a thousand fans attending. The following day the arena was officially closed and demolished.
It was rebuilt and reopened in August 2014, financed by the Russian businessman [[Sergey Samsonenko]], built alongside the four-star hotel "Russia".
In September 2015, the west and east stands were upgraded by 500 seats and south and north stands upgraded with 650 seats.
Now the arena is the home ground of [[RK Vardar]], [[ZRK Vardar]] and [[KK MZT Skopje|MZT Skopje]]. Sports Centre Jane Sandanski has a fitness centre, aerobics centre, tennis and paddle tennis courts, playground for children and exclusive HUMMEL sports store and fan shop.
==External links== * [http://scjanesandanski.mk/mk-MK/Home/Page/4 Official website] in Macedonian and English
