'''Mihter Wendolin''' (born February 3, 1987 in [[Pohnpei]]) is a [[Federated States of Micronesia|Micronesian]] sprinter.<ref>{{cite web |title= Mihter Wendolin |url= http://www.london2012.com/athlete/wendolin-mihter-1090160/ |publisher= London 2012 |accessdate= 2012-08-06 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120827012847/http://www.london2012.com/athlete/wendolin-mihter-1090160/ |archivedate= 2012-08-27}}</ref> She competed in the [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Olympics &ndash; Women's 100 metres|100 metres]] competition at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]]; she ran the preliminaries in 13.67 seconds, which did not qualify her for Round 1.<ref>{{cite web |title=Women's 100m Results: Preliminaries |url= http://www.london2012.com/athletics/event/women-100m/phase=atw001p00/index.html |publisher= London 2012 |accessdate= 2012-08-06}}</ref>
