{{More citations needed|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Stade Abbé-Deschamps<ref>http://www.aja.fr/index.php/le-stade-abbe-deschamps.html</ref> | nickname = l'Abbé-Deschamps | image = Auxerre - Stade Abbé-Deschamps (41).jpg | image_size = 250px | fullname = Stade Abbé-Deschamps | location = Route de Vaux, 89006, [[Auxerre]], [[France]] | coordinates = {{Coord|47|47|12.31|N|3|35|19.19|E|}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1905 | renovated = 1994 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[AJ Auxerre]] | operator = AJ Auxerre | surface = [[Grass]] | construction_cost = | architect = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[AJ Auxerre]] | seating_capacity = 18,541 | dimensions = 110 x 60m }} The '''Stade Abbé-Deschamps''' is the home of [[AJ Auxerre]] football club in [[Auxerre]], [[France]]. It has a capacity of 24,493. Renovated in 1994, it was renamed the '''Stade Abbé-Deschamps''' after Abbé Deschamps, who founded the club in 1905.<ref>http://www.aja.fr/</ref>
